                                                                                                 61
                                                                                                    In certain email applications where received messages are stored and decrypted at a later time, the cryptoperiod of
                                                                                                    a private key-transport key may exceed the cryptoperiod of the public key-transport key.
                                                                                                 62
                                                                                                    In certain email applications where received messages are stored and decrypted at a later time, the key’s recipient-
                                                                                                    usage period key may exceed the originator-usage period.
                                                                                                 63
                                                                                                    In certain email applications where received messages are stored and decrypted at a later time, the cryptoperiod of
                                                                                                    a private static key-agreement key may exceed the cryptoperiod of the corresponding public static key-agreement
                                                                                                    key.




